## Task: Limit initial log output in web UI to last 1000 lines with load-more

Default log display in the web UI should only show the last 1000 lines of output per run.

## Behavior
- Initial page load shows the last 1000 lines of log output
- Include a button to retrieve/load previous log output (pagination backwards)
- If logs are streaming (follow mode), the initial load still starts with the last 1000 lines
- If streamed output causes displayed lines to exceed 1000, that's fine — only the initial load is capped
- Applies to individual run log views
